RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 22500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. MURUMBI raced off the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the bend in the four path, swung wide into the stretch and improved position in the lane while drifting out some in the final furlong. TRUE ATKA raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path and gained ground mildly in the stretch while never threatening the top two. LIZZ A BEE trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, swung wide into the stretch and made no bid. SOUTHERN SMILE led the field on the inside through the opening quarter, dueled from the two path around the bend and tired in the stretch.
